result.execSummary:
The defendant Elliott Gene Kyles was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession with Intent to Deliver Heroin (<=3g), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(d)1.
  • Possess with Intent to Deliver Cocaine (>1-5g), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(cm)1r.
  • Possess with Intent to Deliver Deliver Narcotics, a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(a).
  • Possession of a Firearm by a Felon, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
